subject: p13263843
Findings: Comparison study of, there is again extensive opacification involving much of the right hemithorax. This is consistent with a previous study showing substantial loculation of right pleural fluid collection with underlying extensive volume loss. Prominence of markings on the left most likely represents redistribution of blood flow to non-aerated regions on the right.
